         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels"><bibl><title corresp="ref:hartmannju1987"/><citedRange>92-95</citedRange></bibl></note><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment">cf. 2.8a <hi>ata evābhinirhṛtya</hi>.</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment"><hi>/// te</hi>: either 2.8d <hi>te</hi> or 2.9b <hi>namo'rhate</hi>. <hi>to</hi> might be <distinct type="ms_text">to[_s](_a_ṣ\)</distinct> 'these', but a precise parallel in the Skt. text is not found.</note><note corresp="#b1" type="philcomment">: restoration uncertain. <hi>wmār</hi> 'jewel' as the translation of Skt. <hi>ratna</hi>, frequent in these strophes, is excluded.</note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment">either 2.11a–b <hi>rūparatnātmabhāvāya cittaratnāntarātmane</hi> or 2.13a–b <hi>namas te rūparatnāya  cittara(tnā)ya te nama(ḥ)</hi> (in the latter case, it would provide the <hi>tnā</hi> restored by <bibl><title corresp="ref:hartmannju1987"/><citedRange>95</citedRange></bibl>).</note><note corresp="#b3" type="philcomment"><hi>wināsam</hi>: probably <hi>(ci) wināsam</hi> 'I honour you' v.s., as a translation of e.g. 2.11d, 2.12d, 2.13b, 2.13d <hi>te namaḥ</hi>.</note></p>
         </div>
